equation_narrative.headline: Polar context from structural contacts drives Q selection over charged alternatives
equation_narrative.story: Position 31 in ubiquitin sits in a charged local environment (VKAKI[Q]DKEGI) with 7 structural contacts. Through layers 1-23, the model assembles a representation that shifts from hydrophobic-leaning (L dominates at 36% by L10) to polar/small (S/T lead L10-25). The representation character reflects the model reading structural contacts and local sequence context, not making predictions. At L25, the decision phase begins: Q-specific prediction channels activate (F30:7029, N26:2264), and Q rises from 13% to 75% by L33. The decisive evidence is the combination of polar structural environment and the need for a medium-length polar side chain, which Q satisfies better than charged alternatives E and K.

perception_phase.summary: Layers 1-23 gather structural and sequence context. The model reads 7 structural contacts through attention heads (L26:H4 with 0.979 structural attention erases -3.7 from Q, suggesting initial hydrophobic bias from contacts). Early layers show hydrophobic character: L peaks at 36% at L10, consistent with buried contacts being read. By L15-23, the representation shifts toward polar/small residues (S leads at 24% by L15), reflecting integration of local charged context (K at 29, K at 33, D at 34). SAE features at L18 show moderate activation (F18:6256 at 14.6 proj, F18:4071 at 14.4 proj) without strong AA-specificity, indicating context assembly rather than prediction. The logit lens shows frequent lead changes (10 total through L25), characteristic of evolving representation character rather than committed prediction.
perception_phase.context_character: By L23, the representation encodes a polar/charged local environment with moderate burial. The immediate sequence context is lysine-rich (K at 29, 33) with acidic residues nearby (D at 34, E at 36), suggesting a surface-exposed or interface position requiring polar character.
key_information_sources: Structural contacts: 7 residues within contact distance, read primarily through L26:H4 (0.979 structural attention) and L20:H13 (0.722 structural attention)
Co-evolutionary signal: 1 coupled position detected, indicating modest functional constraint
Local sequence: charged context (K29, K33, D34, E36) integrated through local attention heads (L11:H2 with 0.897 local attention)
L18 features: F18:6256 and F18:4071 (14.6, 14.4 proj) encode general polar context without AA-specificity

decision_phase.summary: The decision crystallizes at L25-26 when Q-specific prediction channels activate. N26:2264 fires with 1.313 projection toward Q (also supporting K and R, indicating polar/charged selectivity). L29-30 show strong Q commitment: N29:1477 (0.855 proj), N29:1046 (0.720 proj), and N30:3979 (0.660 proj) all vote specifically for Q. F30:7029 (25.95 proj, MLP source) acts as a major Q prediction channel. Q rises from 13% at L23 to 55% at L29 to 75% at L33, while E (the main charged alternative) peaks at 22% at L30 but collapses to 2.2% by L33.
decision_phase.transition: At L23-25, the representation transitions from context encoding to prediction. L24 shows the first strong Q-specific MLP neuron (N24:534 with 0.551 proj), and L25 MLP contributes +2.99 to Q (the largest MLP boost in the decision phase). SAE features shift from general context encoders to AA-specific prediction channels: F24 features show moderate activation (9.81 max proj) while F30 features show strong Q-specific projection (F30:7029 at 25.95).

candidates.narrative: Q emerges as the clear winner starting at L25 when prediction channels activate. N26:2264 provides the strongest single-neuron vote (1.313 proj), followed by sustained support from L29-30 neurons (N29:1477 at 0.855, N29:1046 at 0.720). F30:7029 (MLP-sourced SAE feature, 25.95 proj) acts as a major prediction channel. Q rises from 13% at L23 to 55% at L29, peaking at 82% at L32 before settling at 75%. The model's confidence reflects Q's ability to satisfy both the polar requirement (from local context) and medium side-chain length (distinguishing it from smaller S/T).
candidates.key_layers: Emerges at L25, dominant by L29, peaks at L32
key_evidence: N26:2264 (1.313 proj) — strongest Q-specific neuron, also votes K/R indicating polar/charged selectivity
F30:7029 (MLP, 25.95 proj) — major Q prediction channel
N29:1477 (0.855 proj), N29:1046 (0.720 proj) — sustained L29 support
L28-29 velocity: +6.7 total delta (L28), driven by both attention (+3.68) and MLP (+3.02)

candidates.narrative: E is the main charged alternative, rising from 5% at L23 to peak at 22% at L30 before collapsing to 2.2% by L33. E benefits from the charged local context (K29, K33, D34) and receives support from early decision neurons (N14:4712 votes E at 0.392, Q at 0.295). However, E loses decisively in L30-33: strong E-erasing neurons activate (N30:4229 votes against Q at -0.636 while voting P/D/L), and attention heads push away from E (L32:H15 erases -1.778). The model ultimately rejects E in favor of Q's polar-but-neutral character.
candidates.key_layers: Rises L23-30, peaks at L30 (22%), collapses L30-33
key_evidence: N14:4712 (0.392 proj to E, 0.295 to Q) — early E support
N30:4229 (-0.636 Q proj) votes P/D/L, contributing to E's decline

candidates.narrative: S leads the logit lens from L11-25, peaking at 24% at L15. This reflects the representation's polar/small character during the perception phase, not a model prediction. The model is assembling a representation consistent with small polar residues as it integrates structural contacts and local sequence. S's prominence indicates the representation encodes 'polar and potentially small' character. Once AA-specific prediction channels activate at L24+, S loses ground rapidly (19.6% at L25 to final insignificance), as the model commits to Q's longer side chain.
key_evidence: Logit lens lead L11-25 reflects polar/small representation character
F18:3516 (MLP) erases -0.326 from Q while voting S at 0.561 — encodes small-polar context
Rapid decline post-L25 as Q-specific channels activate

candidates.narrative: K maintains 3-4% through the decision phase, supported by the charged local context (K at positions 29 and 33). N26:2264 votes K at 0.736 (second to Q at 1.313), indicating the model considers charged alternatives. However, K never gains traction in the decision phase, suggesting the model reads position 31 as requiring neutral polar character rather than positive charge. K peaks at 10% at L25 but remains a minor contender throughout.
candidates.key_layers: Stable at 3-4% L23-33, peaks at L25 (10%)
key_evidence: N26:2264 votes K at 0.736 (Q at 1.313) — charged alternative consideration
Local context: K29, K33 provide charged environment

candidates.narrative: L dominates the early logit lens (36% at L10), reflecting the hydrophobic character of structural contacts being read in layers 5-10. This is not a prediction but rather the representation's correlation with hydrophobic residues as the model processes buried contacts. L's early prominence shows the model initially encodes 'hydrophobic contact environment' before integrating the charged local sequence context. L declines as polar context accumulates, dropping below 5% by L17.
key_evidence: L10 peak (36%) reflects hydrophobic structural contacts in representation
N17:1080 erases -0.199 from Q while voting F/T/V — hydrophobic context encoding
Decline coincides with polar context integration L15-20

turning_points.description: The representation shifts from hydrophobic to polar character. L drops from 36% to below 15% as S/T rise to 24%. This reflects the model integrating charged local sequence context (K29, K33, D34) with the initial structural contact information. Attention heads shift from structural reading to local sequence reading: L11:H2 shows 0.897 local attention, erasing -2.893 from Q. The logit lens lead changes from L to T to S, tracking the representation's evolving chemical character from hydrophobic-buried to polar-surface.

The perception-to-decision transition occurs. L25 MLP contributes +2.99 to Q (largest MLP boost), and Q takes the logit lens lead for the first time (19.0% vs S at 19.6%). N26:2264 fires with 1.313 projection, the strongest single Q vote in the entire network. This marks the shift from 'assembling polar context' to 'predicting Q specifically'. SAE features transition from general context encoders (F24 max 9.81 proj) to AA-specific channels (F30:7029 at 25.95 proj).

Q commitment solidifies while E is rejected. L29 shows strong Q support (N29:1477 at 0.855, N29:1046 at 0.720, total MLP +2.41) pushing Q from 55% to peak trajectory. L30 is decisive for E's collapse: E peaks at 22% but strong erasure neurons activate (N30:4229 at -0.636 Q proj votes P/D/L instead). The model resolves the polar-vs-charged ambiguity in favor of neutral polar (Q) over acidic (E). Q rises to 75% while E drops to 14% by L30.

deep_dives.label: Structural attention L20-26
deep_dives.caption: L26:H4 (0.979 structural attention, -3.711 proj) and L20:H13 (0.722 structural attention, -2.404 proj) read structural contacts. These heads erase from Q, suggesting initial hydrophobic bias from buried contacts that must be overcome by local charged context.

deep_dives.label: Context assembly L18
deep_dives.caption: L18 features encode general polar context without AA-specificity. F18:6256 (14.61 proj) and F18:4071 (14.44 proj) show the representation is polar-leaning but not yet committed to a specific amino acid. This is context encoding, not prediction.

deep_dives.label: Decision onset L24-26
deep_dives.caption: The transition from perception to decision. L24 shows first strong Q-specific neuron (N24:534 at 0.551). L25 MLP delivers +2.99 boost. L26:N2264 provides strongest single vote (1.313) with polar/charged selectivity (also votes K/R). Watch total_answer_proj shift from modest to decisive.

deep_dives.label: Q prediction channels L30
deep_dives.caption: L30 features are Q-specific prediction channels. F30:7029 (MLP, 25.95 proj), F30:2604 (MLP, 24.12 proj), and F30:2663 (MLP, 23.31 proj) show high Q-specificity. These are the model's committed Q votes, distinct from earlier context-encoding features.

deep_dives.label: Q commitment vs E rejection L29-30
deep_dives.caption: L29 solidifies Q (N29:1477 at 0.855, N29:1046 at 0.720, total +2.41). L30 rejects E (N30:4229 at -0.636 votes P/D/L instead, total -2.31). This is where the model resolves polar-neutral (Q) vs polar-charged (E). Compare top_writers (Q-specific) vs top_erasers (anti-Q, pro-other).

deep_dives.label: Final refinement L28-33
deep_dives.caption: L28 shows largest velocity event (+6.7 delta, both attention +3.68 and MLP +3.02 driving toward Q). L32-33 show oscillation (L32: -3.11 attention-driven away, L33: +2.95 MLP-driven toward) as the model fine-tunes the final 75% confidence. This is calibration, not decision-making.

equation_narrative.resolution: The model correctly predicts Q by assembling a polar local context (K29, K33, D34, E36) that overrides initial hydrophobic structural contact signals. The decisive evidence comes at L25-26 when Q-specific prediction channels activate (N26:2264 at 1.313 proj, F30:7029 at 25.95 proj), and the model commits to neutral polar (Q) over charged alternatives (E peaks at 22% L30 but collapses to 2.2%). The 75% confidence reflects Q's optimal fit: polar enough for the charged environment, but neutral and medium-length rather than small (S/T) or charged (E/K).
